# Files the upstream CMake install stages but that we intentionally do not ship,
# listed here so dh_missing treats the omission as deliberate rather than
# aborting the build.
#
# - the upstream systemd unit (staged at an absolute /lib/systemd/system via
#   NSCP_SYSTEMD_UNITDIR): we install our own debian/nsclient.service (PID in
#   /run, systemd-managed RuntimeDirectory/LogsDirectory) to
#   /usr/lib/systemd/system via dh_installsystemd instead. See debian/rules.
# - the /var/log placeholder: the log directory is created at runtime by the
#   unit's LogsDirectory, with the right ownership for the service user, so the
#   package ships no root-owned placeholder.
# - the web frontend stub: web/CMakeLists.txt copies web/dist/* when populated,
#   and upstream accidentally ships a stub web/dist/index.html (a Vite template
#   referencing assets that do not exist). This agent-only package has no web
#   frontend, so it is intentionally not shipped (reported upstream).
# - the bundled upstream license.txt: not read at runtime (only the Windows MSI
#   references it); the licensing is already covered by debian/copyright, so the
#   redundant copy under the private libdir is not shipped.
lib/systemd/system/nsclient.service
var/log/nsclient/nsclient.log
usr/lib/nsclient/web/index.html
usr/lib/nsclient/license.txt
